==English==

===Etymology===
Greek [[platy]] (flat) + [[pous]] (foot).

===Noun===
'''platypus''' (plural: '''platypuses''')
{{wikipedia}}
# An [[egg]]-[[laying]], semi[[aquatic]] [[mammal]] with a [[bill]] like that of a [[duck]], a [[tail]] like that of a [[beaver]], a [[waterproof]] [[pelt]], and (in males) flat webbed feet with [[poisonous]] [[spurs]] on the inside of the back legs.  The platypus, ([[Ornithorhynchus anatinus]]) lives in the freshwater streams of [[Tasmania]] and eastern [[Australia]].

